HEADWORD: Coliseum
<hw>Col`i*se"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. (cf. It.
<ets>coliseo</ets>, <ets>colosseo</ets>), fr. L. <ets>colosseus</ets>
colossal, fr. <ets>colossus</ets> a colossus. See <er>Colossus</er>, and
cf. <er>Colosseum</er>.]</ety> <def>The amphitheater of Vespasian at
Rome, the largest in the world.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Colosseum</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

